<AbstractNarration>HRD 03-28623&lt;br/&gt;Dr. Lisa A. Pruitt is a professor of Biomedical Engineering at University of California at Berkley.  Mentoring is a significant part of the undergraduate research program in Biomedical Engineering and is incorporated into the development of curriculum in this program.  A training aspect to her program seeks to develop mentoring skills in students who may serve as peer mentors.  Dr. Pruitt serves as a mentor and as an excellent role model.</AbstractNarration>
